The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Bengal | Runaway trio
                                                                                                               Runaway trio
                            
	Calcutta, April 15: Railway police detained at Jadavpur station three teenagers who had fled home after failing in their Class VIII exams. The girls are from South 24-Parganas Mograhat, about 55km away.        
	Snatcher caught        
	Police caught a man fleeing with a womans purse and chain at Krishnagar station. He was identified as Rajesh Das, 27, of Barrackpore.                                                                                                                                                                             
